description: How to Create a Digital Planner with Hyperlinks in Canva. Open Canva and create a new design with "US Letter" dimensions. Pick a background that suits your style. For this example, I‚Äôve used a grey wood background, but feel free to choose what you like best. Insert a rectangle shape, choose your preferred color, and position it in the center of the design. Search for a binder ring element in Canva‚Äôs library to give your planner a realistic touch. Add rectangle shapes for your tabs. You can add as many tabs as you need for different sections of the planner. Select all your tabs, align them properly, and send them to the back layer. To make your design more lifelike, add shadows to your tabs. I recommend using a line shadow, sending it to the back, and reducing the transparency for a subtle effect. Follow the same steps to add a shadow to your binder ring for a consistent look. If you need more tabs at the top of the planner, repeat the previous steps: align, send them to the back, and apply shadows. Add text to each tab to indicate the section they represent. Customize your planner‚Äôs cover to match your style and theme. Create the inner pages of your planner, such as daily, weekly, and monthly layouts. Label each page so it‚Äôs easier to organize and link them later. To hyperlink your tabs or text, select the text, click on the three dots, and choose "Link." Then, select the corresponding page to link to. Once everything is set, download your planner as a PDF. Open your planner in a note-taking app like GoodNotes to start using it. Congratulations! Your digital planner is ready to use.   For more tutorials, check out my playlist at the top of my profile, including guides on selling Canva templates or digital products on Beacons. #howtoselldigitalproducts #digitalproductstosell #digitalproducts #canvahacks #digitalplanner

description: To replace the battery in your PlayStation 4 (PS4) controller, you can follow these simple steps: 1. Use a small screwdriver to gently remove the 4 screws on the back of the controller. 2. Carefully remove the back plate and detach the battery from the controller. 3. Take note of the battery's model number and purchase a new one online or at a gaming store. 4. Insert the new battery into the controller and reattach the back plate. 5. Replace the 4 screws on the back of the controller. Some tips, tricks, and hacks to help extend the life of your PS4 controller battery include: - Turning off the controller when not in use. - Lowering the controller's brightness or vibration settings to conserve battery life. - Using a charging dock or cable to charge the controller instead of leaving it plugged in all the time. - Using a second controller while the first one charges to avoid interruptions in your gaming sessions. - Keeping your controller away from extreme temperatures, which can damage the battery. By following these simple steps and taking care of your PS4 controller's battery, you can enjoy long-lasting gaming sessions without interruption.  #PS4Tips #ps4gamer #ps4 #videogames #GamerLife #GamingTips #ps4repair #playstation #ps4tricks #ps4players #controller #playstationvsxbox #ps5 #playstation4 #playstationcontroller #retrogamer #playstationaddict #playstationbrasil@ #playstationcommunity #playstationcollection #playstationexclusive #playstationfrance #playstationgreece #playstationgaming #playstationhack #playstationhits #playstationmexico #ps4secrets

description: 3 WEEK ITINERARY for NORWAY üá≥üá¥üèîÔ∏èüåø You start this itinerary in Bod√∏ in the North of Norway. The best time is in the summer months. Plan at least three weeks for this route! üìå Steigen The area around Steigen is located north of Bod√∏ and you should definitely visit it before taking the ferry from Bod√∏ to Moskenes (Lofoten). It‚Äôs a lot less touristy here, but no less beautiful. Definitely visit B√∏sanden beach! üìå Lofoten You arrive in the very south of Lofoten, in Moskenes (Ferry Harbor). You can now spend the next few days exploring the Lofoten Islands. These are my favorite places: Reine & Reinebringen Hike, Kvalvika Beach & Ryten Hike, Hauklandstranda & Mannen Hike, Henningsv√¶r, Delpen Hike. If you are planning to explore the area by campervan, please refrain from wild camping out of consideration for nature and the locals! üìå And√∏ya The island of And√∏ya is located to the north of Lofoten. It‚Äôs definitely worth making a little detour here! There is a great campsite on the beautiful kilometer-long beach of Bleik and you can book a trip to the island of Bleiks√∏ya to see the puffins! The hike to Matinden is also highly recommended. üìå Senja  Take the ferry from Andenes to Gryllefjord to get to Senja. (Please note: the ferry only operates in the summer months!)  On Senja, visit the beautiful viewpoint Tungeneset, as well as the beach Ersfjord and hike to Hesten with a great view of Segla! üìå Nordkapp From Senja, it‚Äôs still a relatively long way to Nordkapp, the northernmost point on the European mainland. It‚Äôs worth stopping in the city of Troms√∏ on the way. The further north you drive, the higher your chances of encountering free-roaming reindeer! #mountains #nature #Outdoors #roadtrip #norway #lofoten #norwegen #Hiking #bergliebe #travel

description: Replying to @mo we sell 2mL sample bottles of each and every single one of our ritual oils. As much as we would love to send out perfume swatches those things are extremely labor and cost intensive. Even the supposed free swatches that one would get from magazines come from multi million dollar corporations and cost a lot of money  which you ultimately pay for when you buy the magazine or the magazine subscriptions. As much as we would love to  there‚Äôs just no way for us to do that as an independent artisan perfume studio. BUT  once we get a multimillion dollar investor in our corner  we will definitely try to do that. But for now all we can do is make it a little bit more available by selling our 2ml sample vials. Side note: I would like everyone to know that we tried doing free samples  but we quickly learned that some people are dishonest and ordered up our entire stock  leaving none for anybody else to try. At that point  we learned that if we are going to survive in this industry  we are going to have to play by the rules of doing business  just like everybody else. It was a very expensive mistake that almost took out our business  but we learned and evolved. Thank you for taking the time to read this. I know it was a lot  but I do believe that people need to know why we do the things the way that we do. ##independentartist##ritualoil###independentperfume##artisanperfume
